'''dracunculus (dracunculi)'''

==Etymology==
Latin ''[[draco]]'' dragon + ''[[-unculus]]'' [[diminutive]] ending

==Noun==

# A small [[dragon]].
# (''Phylogeny'') A [[genus]] of [[spiruroid]] [[nematode]] [[parasite]]s in the family Dracunculidae.  ''Dracunculus medinensis'' is an extremely long [[worm]] which causes a [[burn]]ing rash up the leg of humans, explaining the choice of genus name.

